1
00:00:05,182 --> 00:00:08,492
In this world the most valuable treasure

2
00:00:08,492 --> 00:00:10,920
is to get the association of devotees,

3
00:00:10,920 --> 00:00:13,964
and what do we get in their association?

4
00:00:13,964 --> 00:00:16,032
They tell us about Kṛṣṇa.

5
00:00:16,032 --> 00:00:18,720
[Nectar or Poison?]

6
00:00:19,102 --> 00:00:22,269
Śravaṇa-mańgalam. Hearing about Kṛṣṇa

7
00:00:22,269 --> 00:00:29,343
is the beginning of auspiciousness
in one's life.

8
00:00:30,744 --> 00:00:35,839
Bhuvi gṛṇanti te bhūri-dā janāḥ
(SB: 10.31.9),

9
00:00:35,839 --> 00:00:40,807
and in the world, those who do this are

10
00:00:40,807 --> 00:00:48,548
the ultimate humanitarians,
philanthropists,

11
00:00:51,390 --> 00:00:54,653
saviours of the world.

12
00:00:55,269 --> 00:01:00,776
In so many places,
so much has been said

13
00:01:00,778 --> 00:01:06,238
in favour of hearing about Kṛṣṇa.

14
00:01:07,382 --> 00:01:09,215
But Sanātan Goswāmī is saying,

15
00:01:09,215 --> 00:01:12,718
“Avaiṣṇava-mukhodgīrṇaḿ
pūtaḿ Hari-kathāmṛtam

16
00:01:12,779 --> 00:01:15,083
śravaṇaḿ naiva kartavyaḿ”
(Padma Purāṇa),

17
00:01:15,083 --> 00:01:19,693
but don't hear about Kṛṣṇa

18
00:01:19,848 --> 00:01:25,635
from someone
who's not actually a vaiṣṇava.

19
00:01:26,274 --> 00:01:28,932
What will be the effect?

20
00:01:28,932 --> 00:01:36,279
He says, sarpa ucchiṣṭa,
“Sarpocchiṣṭaḿ yathā payaḥ.”

21
00:01:36,279 --> 00:01:40,520
In Vedic understanding, feeding a snake,

22
00:01:40,520 --> 00:01:45,988
a cobra, milk, will increase its venom;

23
00:01:46,051 --> 00:01:51,527
the milk becomes poisonous,
it's converted into poison.

24
00:01:51,577 --> 00:01:55,769
It’s milk, but given to a cobra
it’s converted into poison.

25
00:01:55,769 --> 00:01:59,699
Hari-kathā is that nectarine substance,
it should be,

26
00:01:59,699 --> 00:02:03,737
that you should hear about,
remember, chant.

27
00:02:03,737 --> 00:02:08,948
Śravaṇam, kīrtanam, Kṛṣṇa.

28
00:02:08,948 --> 00:02:17,171
But not from a non-devotee,
a non-vaiṣṇava,

29
00:02:17,191 --> 00:02:20,923
someone who's not initiated

30
00:02:20,923 --> 00:02:26,317
into Kṛṣṇa conception by
a substantial agent;

31
00:02:26,598 --> 00:02:29,376
it will have the opposite effect—

32
00:02:29,376 --> 00:02:33,069
what is supposed to be life saving,

33
00:02:33,069 --> 00:02:38,984
life giving nectar, is rendered poison.

